<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,1466,2012]" lastBlockId="28.[151,1437,152,1338]" lastPageId="28" lastPageNumber="29" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
DIAGNOSIS. 
<taxonomicName box="[373,503,1747,1772]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Bechynella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[373,503,1747,1772]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Bechynella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[513,594,1746,1772]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
was previously confused with the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1092,1224,1747,1772]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Serraphula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1092,1224,1747,1772]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Serraphula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from which it is easily distinguishable mainly for having: a) apical spur of the hind tibiae short, not serrate (
<figureCitation box="[1220,1305,1786,1812]" captionStart="FIGURES 83 – 86" captionStartId="43.[151,269,1105,1129]" captionTargetBox="[150,1433,182,1091]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURES 83 – 86. Morphological characters in Bechynella gen. n.: hind tibia of B. bohumilae (Bechyné) (83); ventral side of first anterior tarsomere in male of B. bohumilae (Bechyné) (84); metafemoral spring of B. pallens (Bechyné) (85); head of B. bohumilae (Bechyné) (86)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195021/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Fig. 
<number box="[1275,1305,1786,1812]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="83.0">83</number>
</figureCitation>
) (in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Serraphula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Serraphula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
hind apical spur clearly serrate and formed by a narrow and laterally bent foil folded in an evident dorsal furrow [
<figureCitation box="[289,432,1866,1892]" captionStart="FIGURES 23 – 30" captionStartId="37.[151,269,1913,1937]" captionTargetBox="[251,1349,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURES 23 – 30. Morphological characters in Serraphula Jacoby: apical spur of hind tibiae of S. aenea Jacoby (23); ibidem S. audisiana sp. n. (24); ibidem S. elongata Jacoby (25); ibidem S. monticola sp. n. (26); ibidem S. osellai sp. n. (27); ibidem S. puncticollis Bryant (28); metafemoral spring of S. elongata Jacoby (29); head of S. elongata Jacoby (30)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195015/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Figs 
<number box="[351,432,1866,1892]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="25.5" valueMax="28.0" valueMin="23.0">23–28</number>
</figureCitation>
]); b) antennae inserted ahead, near the distal ocular margin (
<figureCitation box="[1157,1244,1866,1892]" captionStart="FIGURES 83 – 86" captionStartId="43.[151,269,1105,1129]" captionTargetBox="[150,1433,182,1091]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURES 83 – 86. Morphological characters in Bechynella gen. n.: hind tibia of B. bohumilae (Bechyné) (83); ventral side of first anterior tarsomere in male of B. bohumilae (Bechyné) (84); metafemoral spring of B. pallens (Bechyné) (85); head of B. bohumilae (Bechyné) (86)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195021/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Fig. 
<number box="[1214,1244,1866,1892]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="86.0">86</number>
</figureCitation>
) (in 
<taxonomicName box="[1304,1436,1867,1892]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Serraphula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1304,1436,1867,1892]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Serraphula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
antennae inserted medially between eyes [
<figureCitation box="[643,734,1906,1932]" captionStart="FIGURES 23 – 30" captionStartId="37.[151,269,1913,1937]" captionTargetBox="[251,1349,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURES 23 – 30. Morphological characters in Serraphula Jacoby: apical spur of hind tibiae of S. aenea Jacoby (23); ibidem S. audisiana sp. n. (24); ibidem S. elongata Jacoby (25); ibidem S. monticola sp. n. (26); ibidem S. osellai sp. n. (27); ibidem S. puncticollis Bryant (28); metafemoral spring of S. elongata Jacoby (29); head of S. elongata Jacoby (30)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195015/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Fig. 
<number box="[699,734,1906,1932]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="30.0">30</number>
</figureCitation>
]); c) pronotum shorter (LE/LP ≥ 
<number box="[1120,1176,1906,1932]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="3.4">3.40</number>
), laterally clearly subparallel, with anterior and posterior angles bearing a very long seta (in 
<taxonomicName box="[995,1127,1947,1972]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Serraphula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[995,1127,1947,1972]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Serraphula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
pronotum longer [usually LE/LP &lt;
<number box="[260,317,1986,2012]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="3.4">3.40</number>
], laterally sub-rounded, and without long setae at the anterior and posterior angles); d) first and middle tarsomeres in male ventrally with adhesive setigerous area not visible by means of stereomicroscope and shaped as in 
<figureCitation box="[362,448,192,218]" captionStart="FIGURES 83 – 86" captionStartId="43.[151,269,1105,1129]" captionTargetBox="[150,1433,182,1091]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURES 83 – 86. Morphological characters in Bechynella gen. n.: hind tibia of B. bohumilae (Bechyné) (83); ventral side of first anterior tarsomere in male of B. bohumilae (Bechyné) (84); metafemoral spring of B. pallens (Bechyné) (85); head of B. bohumilae (Bechyné) (86)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195021/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Fig. 
<number box="[419,448,192,218]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="84.0">84</number>
</figureCitation>
(in 
<taxonomicName box="[501,633,192,217]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Serraphula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[501,633,192,217]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Serraphula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
first and middle tarsomeres in male ventrally with setigerous area clearly visible by means of stereomicroscope and shaped as 
<figureCitation box="[853,988,232,258]" captionStart="FIGURES 77 – 82" captionStartId="42.[151,269,1534,1558]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,183,1498]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURES 77 – 82. Ventral side of first anterior and middle tarsomeres in male and female of Serraphula elongata Jacoby: male with differentiated adhesive structure (77, 79, 81 – 82); female without differentiated adhesive structure (78, 80)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195020/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Figs 
<number box="[910,988,232,258]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="79.5" valueMax="82.0" valueMin="77.0">77–82</number>
</figureCitation>
); e) metafemoral spring attributable to the 
<taxonomicName box="[194,355,272,297]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Chaetocnema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[194,355,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Chaetocnema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
morpho-group (
<bibRefCitation author="Furth" box="[547,799,272,298]" pageId="28" pageNumber="30" refString="Furth, D. G. &amp; Suzuki, K. (1998) Studies of Oriental and Australian Alticinae genera based on the comprative morphology of the metafemoral spring, genitalia, and hind wing venation. In: Biondi, M., Daccordi, M. &amp; Furth, D. G. (Eds.), P roceedings of the Fourth International Symposium on the Chrysomelidae. Proceedings of XX I. C. E. Firenze, 1996. Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali, Torino, pp. 91 - 124." type="journal article" year="1998">
Furth &amp; Suzuki 
<number box="[739,799,272,298]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="1998.0">1998</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) (
<figureCitation box="[824,909,272,298]" captionStart="FIGURES 83 – 86" captionStartId="43.[151,269,1105,1129]" captionTargetBox="[150,1433,182,1091]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURES 83 – 86. Morphological characters in Bechynella gen. n.: hind tibia of B. bohumilae (Bechyné) (83); ventral side of first anterior tarsomere in male of B. bohumilae (Bechyné) (84); metafemoral spring of B. pallens (Bechyné) (85); head of B. bohumilae (Bechyné) (86)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195021/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Fig. 
<number box="[879,909,272,298]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="85.0">85</number>
</figureCitation>
) (in 
<taxonomicName box="[966,1098,272,297]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Serraphula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[966,1098,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Serraphula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
metafemoral spring attributable to the 
<taxonomicName box="[283,403,312,337]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Psylliodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[283,403,312,337]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Psylliodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
morpho-group [
<bibRefCitation author="Furth" box="[596,853,312,338]" pageId="28" pageNumber="30" refString="Furth, D. G. &amp; Suzuki, K. (1998) Studies of Oriental and Australian Alticinae genera based on the comprative morphology of the metafemoral spring, genitalia, and hind wing venation. In: Biondi, M., Daccordi, M. &amp; Furth, D. G. (Eds.), P roceedings of the Fourth International Symposium on the Chrysomelidae. Proceedings of XX I. C. E. Firenze, 1996. Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali, Torino, pp. 91 - 124." type="journal article" year="1998">
Furth &amp; Suzuki 
<number box="[792,853,312,338]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="1998.0">1998</number>
</bibRefCitation>
] [
<figureCitation box="[876,968,312,338]" captionStart="FIGURES 23 – 30" captionStartId="37.[151,269,1913,1937]" captionTargetBox="[251,1349,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURES 23 – 30. Morphological characters in Serraphula Jacoby: apical spur of hind tibiae of S. aenea Jacoby (23); ibidem S. audisiana sp. n. (24); ibidem S. elongata Jacoby (25); ibidem S. monticola sp. n. (26); ibidem S. osellai sp. n. (27); ibidem S. puncticollis Bryant (28); metafemoral spring of S. elongata Jacoby (29); head of S. elongata Jacoby (30)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195015/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Fig. 
<number box="[933,968,312,338]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="29.0">29</number>
</figureCitation>
]). 
<taxonomicName box="[997,1127,312,337]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Bechynella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[997,1127,312,337]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Bechynella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1136,1215,312,338]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
shows some similarities in external morphology also with the Palaearctic genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Weise, 1887" authorityName="Weise" authorityYear="1887" box="[894,1205,352,378]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Anthobiodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[894,1041,352,377]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Anthobiodes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Weise" box="[1057,1205,352,378]" pageId="28" pageNumber="30" refString="Weise, J. (1887) Anthobiodes n. gen. Halticarum. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, 31, 402." type="journal article" year="1887">
Weise, 
<number box="[1143,1205,352,378]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="1887.0">1887</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. However the latter genus is clearly recognizable for having: a) body shape flatter; b) antennae shorter than body length; c) first metatarsomere shorter, as long as half of hind tibial length; d) apical spur of hind tibiae shorter and less robust.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[198,920,472,498]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,152,1338]" box="[198,920,472,498]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<typeStatus box="[198,271,472,498]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<collectionCode box="[198,271,472,498]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">TYPE</collectionCode>
</typeStatus>
SPECIES. 
<taxonomicName authority="Bechyne, 1955: 517" authorityName="Bechyne" authorityPageNumber="517" authorityYear="1955" box="[407,915,472,498]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Serraphula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bohumilae">
<emphasis box="[407,671,472,497]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Serraphula bohumilae</emphasis>
Bechyné, 
<number box="[794,857,472,498]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="1955.0">1955</number>
